      <scopecontent id="aspace_f46f7ebb52d09e7df2e96e3cf4d254cf">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection is an in-progress oral history on the violin pedagogue Dorothy DeLay (March 31, 1917 – March 24, 2002), who taught at several music conservatories, including the Juilliard School, University of Cincinnati College-Conservatory of Music, during the mid- to late 20th century. The interviews were conducted by Yale undergraduate Keeley Brooks, as the basis of her 2025 senior thesis.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <odd id="aspace_41d9de3a328b21ab626325bbf9836fce">
         <head>General</head>
         <p>All interviews conducted by Keely Brooks, unless otherwise indicated.</p>
      </odd>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_a7b8f4ab95e6bba6153156e9bc853fc2">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>This collection is open for research. The finding aid includes links to stream most interviews online via Oral History of American Music's (OHAM) AV access system, Aviary. Yale users can login to Aviary using their Yale University ID, to stream these interviews without restriction. Other users are able to request access to interviews directly through Aviary. For access instructions, , see <ref href="https://guides.library.yale.edu/oham/collectionsguide/access">OHAM's website.</ref>
         </p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_db92a3e731fc1e01eccdf2540106b714">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Rights and permissions for Oral History of American Music materials vary between individual interviews. Researchers wishing to publish or broadcast Oral History of American Music materials are responsible for obtaining direct authorization from copyright holders: generally, the interviewees or their estates.</p>
      </userestrict>
      <arrangement id="aspace_876724d652b961299afbdd6bfc3548a9">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is arranged alphabetically by surname.</p>
      </arrangement>
